article.headline: Evansville 80, Austin Peay 75
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Kyle Anslinger scored 26 points and had a key assist with 29 seconds left to lead Evansville past Austin Peay 80-75 Monday night. The Purple Aces (8-3) won their fourth straight game by holding off Austin Peay (3-6) in the last minute. Matt Webster hit a layup on a feed from Anslinger with 29 seconds left to make it 76-72. Bradley Strickland followed with a steal and dunk eight seconds later to make it 78-72. Webster added 18 points and Jason Holsinger scored 14 and Strickland added 13 for Evansville, which shot a season-high 62 percent, including 68 percent in the second half. Drake Reed scored 19 for Austin Peay, Derek Wright had 16, reserve Landon Shipley 12 and Fernandez Lockett 10. Austin Peay led 38-29 at the half, but the Purple Aces made 11-of-13 free throws in the second half to pull away. The Governors' last lead was 56-53 with 9:03 left on a 3-pointer by Wes Channels.
